00:08:32,220 --> 00:08:33,960
 "It only ruins the hearers.

220
00:08:33,960 --> 00:08:37,320
 "Do your best to present yourself to God as one approved,

221
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:39,720
 "a worker who has no need to be ashamed,

222
00:08:39,720 --> 00:08:42,200
 "rightly handling the word of truth."

223
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:43,440
 So the first thing that Paul tells us

224
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:45,680
 if you wanna live a life of honor

225
00:08:45,680 --> 00:08:49,200
 is you've gotta avoid unproductive disagreements.

226
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:50,920
 That's your first point.

227
00:08:50,920 --> 00:08:53,180
 You gotta avoid unproductive disagreements.

228
00:08:53,180 --> 00:08:56,040
 He charges Timothy before God.

229
00:08:56,040 --> 00:08:58,040
 Some of your translation says that he charges Timothy

230
00:08:58,040 --> 00:08:59,560
 in the presence of God,

231
00:08:59,560 --> 00:09:01,900
 which is the strongest commissioning

232
00:09:01,900 --> 00:09:05,520
 that Paul gives in any pastoral epistle.

233
00:09:05,520 --> 00:09:07,800
 It would be the ancient Near Eastern equivalent

