1049
00:43:14,940 --> 00:43:19,940
 and he did so so patiently, so astoundingly,

1050
00:43:19,940 --> 00:43:25,400
 that after he surrendered his life to God

1051
00:43:25,400 --> 00:43:27,920
 and he breathed his last,

1052
00:43:27,920 --> 00:43:31,160
 that centurion which stood there by the side

1053
00:43:31,160 --> 00:43:33,960
 said, "Surely that man,

1054
00:43:33,960 --> 00:43:35,960
 "and the way he has suffered so well,

1055
00:43:35,960 --> 00:43:38,160
 "is the son of God."

1056
00:43:38,160 --> 00:43:44,520
 People, they will not be convinced by how strong you are.

1057
00:43:44,520 --> 00:43:47,040
 They will be convinced by how well you suffer.

1058
00:43:47,040 --> 00:43:51,520
 You don't need to retaliate to evil.

1059
00:43:51,520 --> 00:43:55,160
 You need to respond with grace.

1060
00:43:55,160 --> 00:43:56,320
 You need to be patient.

1061
00:43:56,320 --> 00:44:00,500
 And the last one he says is that you should be civil.

1062
00:44:00,500 --> 00:44:03,080
 I love this one, because Paul tells us here

1063
00:44:03,080 --> 00:44:04,960
 at the very end of the letter for all of you,

1064
00:44:04,960 --> 00:44:06,960
 that are, man, you're just kind of uncomfortable

1065
00:44:06,960 --> 00:44:08,200
 in your seat 'cause you wanna get up

1066
00:44:08,200 --> 00:44:09,040
 and you wanna say something.

1067
00:44:09,040 --> 00:44:10,200
 He's like, "Hey, you need to get up

1068
00:44:10,200 --> 00:44:11,300
 "and you need to say something.

1069
00:44:11,300 --> 00:44:12,460
 "There are going to be moments

1070
00:44:12,460 --> 00:44:14,520
 "where you need to correct someone's thinking.

1071
00:44:14,520 --> 00:44:16,920
 "You need to challenge their position.

1072
00:44:16,920 --> 00:44:19,320
 "You need to offer a recommendation.

1073
00:44:19,320 --> 00:44:21,040
 "There are going to be moments where you do that,

1074
00:44:21,040 --> 00:44:22,000
 "and yet, listen to me,

1075
00:44:22,000 --> 00:44:23,780
 "though you may disagree with people,

1076
00:44:23,780 --> 00:44:26,480
 "you always do so with civility."

1077
00:44:26,480 --> 00:44:29,680
 We're bad at this right now.

1078
00:44:30,500 --> 00:44:31,900
 We look across our culture

1079
00:44:31,900 --> 00:44:34,420
 and we see plenty of disagreement,

1080
00:44:34,420 --> 00:44:37,220
 but we see so much indignity.

1081
00:44:37,220 --> 00:44:43,380
 We don't know how to conflict and keep our composure.

1082
00:44:43,380 --> 00:44:47,460
 There's a story that I think articulates

1083
00:44:47,460 --> 00:44:49,340
 what we should do instead so well.

1084
00:44:49,340 --> 00:44:53,180
 It's about 200 years old,

1085
00:44:53,180 --> 00:44:55,780
 the conversation between a guy named Charles Simeon

1086
00:44:55,780 --> 00:45:00,700
 and John Wesley, one was a staunch Calvinist,

1087
00:45:00,700 --> 00:45:03,320
 the other a staunch Arminian.

1088
00:45:03,320 --> 00:45:04,860
 And you don't need to know the distinctions

1089
00:45:04,860 --> 00:45:06,000
 of what those things mean

1090
00:45:06,000 --> 00:45:07,860
 if you've never heard those phrases before,

1091
00:45:07,860 --> 00:45:09,380
 but what you need to know is

1092
00:45:09,380 --> 00:45:12,380
 this was essentially a theological turf battle.

1093
00:45:12,380 --> 00:45:15,760
 These guys, they are doctrinally distinct,

1094
00:45:15,760 --> 00:45:16,600
 to say the least.

1095
00:45:16,600 --> 00:45:18,420
 They are sitting down to have a conversation

1096
00:45:18,420 --> 00:45:20,700
 about their own personal positions,

1097
00:45:20,700 --> 00:45:23,620
 and they know this thing is gonna come to blows

1098
00:45:23,620 --> 00:45:27,300
 because we don't believe similarly on some key issues

1099
00:45:27,300 --> 00:45:29,620
 in areas of the faith.

1100
00:45:29,620 --> 00:45:34,620
 And yet, Charles Simeon, he says this.

1101
00:45:34,620 --> 00:45:38,140
 Speaking to John, he says,

1102
00:45:38,140 --> 00:45:42,540
 "Sir, I understand that you're called an Arminian,

1103
00:45:42,540 --> 00:45:46,700
 and I have been sometimes called a Calvinist.

1104
00:45:46,700 --> 00:45:50,500
 And therefore, I suppose we're to draw daggers.

1105
00:45:51,620 --> 00:45:54,380
 But before I consent to begin that combat

1106
00:45:54,380 --> 00:45:58,480
 with your permission, I'd like to ask a few questions."

1107
00:45:58,480 --> 00:46:04,860
 And what proceeds in the dialogue is Charles asking John,

1108
00:46:04,860 --> 00:46:07,740
 "Do you believe that you are lost

1109
00:46:07,740 --> 00:46:09,260
 in the trespasses of your sin

1110
00:46:09,260 --> 00:46:10,620
 and you cannot save yourself?"

1111
00:46:10,620 --> 00:46:12,160
 Yes, I do believe that.

1112
00:46:12,160 --> 00:46:16,260
 "Do you believe that Jesus Christ is the Son of God

1113
00:46:16,260 --> 00:46:20,040
 and he has come to save your soul?"

1114
00:46:20,040 --> 00:46:22,120
 Yes, I do believe that.

1115
00:46:22,120 --> 00:46:26,180
 "Do you believe God's grace is a gift

1116
00:46:26,180 --> 00:46:29,980
 which we do not earn, we only receive?"

1117
00:46:29,980 --> 00:46:32,180
 Yes, I do believe that, Charles.

1118
00:46:32,180 --> 00:46:37,180
 "Do you believe that your future hope and home is in heaven

1119
00:46:37,180 --> 00:46:40,060
 because he's gone to prepare a place for you?"

1120
00:46:40,060 --> 00:46:42,980
 Yes, I believe that as well.

1121
00:46:42,980 --> 00:46:47,860
 And at the end of his inquisition, Charles looks at John.

1122
00:46:47,860 --> 00:46:52,460
 He says, "Then, sir, with your leave,

1123
00:46:52,460 --> 00:46:55,200
 I will put up my dagger.

1124
00:46:55,200 --> 00:47:00,640
 If you please, instead of searching out our terms

1125
00:47:00,640 --> 00:47:04,840
 and our phrases to be a ground of contention between us,

1126
00:47:04,840 --> 00:47:05,880
 a cause of conflict,

1127
00:47:05,880 --> 00:47:11,320
 let's instead cordially unite with one another

1128
00:47:11,320 --> 00:47:14,600
 in those things upon which we agree."

1129
00:47:17,140 --> 00:47:17,980
 I love it.

1130
00:47:17,980 --> 00:47:21,240
 Charles articulates for us

1131
00:47:21,240 --> 00:47:25,880
 that disagreement is possible

1132
00:47:25,880 --> 00:47:32,440
 without the indignity of robbing someone

1133
00:47:32,440 --> 00:47:35,760
 of their God-given image.

1134
00:47:35,760 --> 00:47:39,200
 And the reason we know it is because at one time,

1135
00:47:39,200 --> 00:47:44,200
 all of who God is disagreed with all of who we are.

1136
00:47:46,920 --> 00:47:48,740
 He's holy.

1137
00:47:48,740 --> 00:47:50,220
 We are unholy.

1138
00:47:50,220 --> 00:47:51,780
 He's loving.

1139
00:47:51,780 --> 00:47:53,140
 We are unloving.

1140
00:47:53,140 --> 00:47:54,940
 He is merciful.

1141
00:47:54,940 --> 00:47:56,500
 We are merciless.

1142
00:47:56,500 --> 00:47:57,980
 He is righteous.

1143
00:47:57,980 --> 00:47:59,340
 We are unrighteous.

1144
00:47:59,340 --> 00:48:00,900
 He is good.

1145
00:48:00,900 --> 00:48:02,380
 And we are evil.

1146
00:48:02,380 --> 00:48:05,300
 And yet, though all of who God is disagreed with,

1147
00:48:05,300 --> 00:48:06,900
 all of who we are,

1148
00:48:06,900 --> 00:48:10,980
 he nonetheless dignified us

1149
00:48:10,980 --> 00:48:12,740
 by sending Jesus

1150
00:48:14,220 --> 00:48:17,600
 to avoid unproductive disagreements

1151
00:48:17,600 --> 00:48:22,100
 and reconcile disparate parties instead,

1152
00:48:22,100 --> 00:48:25,820
 to guard against ungodly influences,

1153
00:48:25,820 --> 00:48:30,040
 teaching us that which is true in the face of a world

1154
00:48:30,040 --> 00:48:35,040
 that specializes in what's false instead.

1155
00:48:35,040 --> 00:48:38,880
 He separated us from worldly passions,

1156
00:48:38,880 --> 00:48:42,480
 dying our death upon our cross

1157
00:48:42,480 --> 00:48:46,520
 and taking our ungodly and worldly passions with them.

1158
00:48:46,520 --> 00:48:52,300
 And he focused on the person past the problem,

1159
00:48:52,300 --> 00:48:55,040
 for he never lost sight of you

1160
00:48:55,040 --> 00:48:58,500
 in his pursuit to save you

1161
00:48:58,500 --> 00:49:00,540
 from that which had condemned you.

1162
00:49:00,540 --> 00:49:02,220
 Don't you see,

1163
00:49:02,220 --> 00:49:07,220
 if you want to live your life with honor,

1164
00:49:07,220 --> 00:49:11,200
 then look to he who died your death.

1165
00:49:12,200 --> 00:49:13,400
 With honor.

1166
00:49:13,400 --> 00:49:16,200
 He is the way.

1167
00:49:16,200 --> 00:49:18,000
 He is the truth.

1168
00:49:18,000 --> 00:49:18,880
 He is the life.

1169
00:49:18,880 --> 00:49:21,400
 And I'm praying you would know him as such.

1170
00:49:21,400 --> 00:49:23,880
 God, we're grateful that we have time now,

1171
00:49:23,880 --> 00:49:27,080
 not just to study some scripture,

1172
00:49:27,080 --> 00:49:29,680
 but God, to hear you speak,

1173
00:49:29,680 --> 00:49:31,720
 not just to sing some songs,

1174
00:49:31,720 --> 00:49:34,800
 but God, celebrate your glory.

1175
00:49:34,800 --> 00:49:40,680
 Not just to feel some conviction

1176
00:49:41,200 --> 00:49:45,760
 but respond to your spirit speaking.

1177
00:49:45,760 --> 00:49:48,640
 It puts us in a spot right now where God,

1178
00:49:48,640 --> 00:49:50,360
 we get to engage with you.

1179
00:49:50,360 --> 00:49:51,360
 We get to respond to you.

1180
00:49:51,360 --> 00:49:53,440
 We get to rejoice for the gospel,

1181
00:49:53,440 --> 00:49:56,000
 which has saved those who believe.

1182
00:49:56,000 --> 00:49:59,440
 God, we want to be honorable

1183
00:49:59,440 --> 00:50:02,160
 in the face of a dishonoring day.

1184
00:50:02,160 --> 00:50:06,360
 And Jesus, it is in you that we see the example

1185
00:50:06,360 --> 00:50:09,120
 and we follow here right now.

1186
00:50:09,120 --> 00:50:10,080
 We love you.

1187
00:50:10,080 --> 00:50:12,720
 It's in your name we pray, amen.

